ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: Have you ever thought about or attempted to end your life?
Notes: 0=Never; 1=It was just a brief passing thought; 2=I have seriously thought about ending my life, but did not plan how or try to do it; 3=I have planned how to end my life, but did not try to do it; 4=I have attempted to end my life

ElementDescription: When I attempted to end my life: I had a plan that I carried out
When I attempted to end my life: I had no plan
When I attempted to end my life: I suddenly felt the urge to attempt to end my life
When I attempted to end my life: I happened to have access to the means to end my life
How often on average have you experienced intense thoughts about ending your life in the past 12 months?
Notes: 0=Never; 1=Less than once a month; 2=Once a month; 3=2-3 times a month; 4=Once a week; 5=2-6 times a week; 6=1 or more times a day

ElementDescription: When you have intense thoughts about ending your life, how long per day does this typically last?
Notes: 0=Not Applicable; 1=Less than 5 minutes; 2=Less than 1 hour; 3=1-4 hours; 4=5-8 hours; 5=More than 8 hours

ElementDescription: When you experience intense thoughts about ending your life, how likely are you to act on them
Notes: 0=Not Applicable; 1=No chance at all; 2=Very Unlikely; 3=Rather Unlikely; 4=Rather likely; 5=Very likely
